It can be different. Right now the default value is taken from the definition of GraphQL schema type. But in case of interface the real value for __typename depends on the returned instance.
For example having this query:
query {
  hero {
    __typename
    name
  }
}

Object hero is defined as  Character in GraphQL schema. So default value will be "Character". But at runtime it can be one of  possible types Human or Droid https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-android/blob/master/apollo-compiler/src/test/graphql/schema.json#L637.
